<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,1169,1557]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,171,1170,1196]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,257,1177,1194]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">REMARKS</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,264,1170,1196]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">.</emphasis>
This is one of the larger 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[555,678,1171,1196]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[555,678,1171,1196]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known to 
<collectingCountry box="[891,942,1171,1197]" name="Peru" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Peru</collectingCountry>
with body lengths of about 
<quantity box="[1265,1388,1169,1197]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="42.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="40.0">40–45 mm</quantity>
and wing spans of more than 
<quantity box="[436,532,1206,1233]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="120.0">120 mm</quantity>
. The dark brown and piceous coloration distinguish it from the other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[1313,1436,1207,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1313,1436,1207,1232]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in 
<collectingCountry box="[268,323,1243,1269]" name="Peru" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
